{"word":"πυρκαιά","slug":"πυρκαιά","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πυρκαιά</b></el> <el>(πυρ-καϊά, <el>epic and ionic</el> <el>ιή, ἡ</el>,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:καίω'><el>καίω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>any place where fire is kindled, a funeral pyre</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a fire, conflagration</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: <i>arson</i>, Lex <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>the flame of love</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}